    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold tracking-tight mb-6">About ArcadeBloom</h1>

    <div class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed space-y-5 text-lg">
        <p>
            ArcadeBloom is a <strong>directory</strong>, not a portal. We find browser games across the web,
            write independent reviews and how-to-play guides for each one, and then send you to the
            original author's site to actually play. We do not host third-party games, wrap them in iframes,
            or pretend they are ours.
        </p>
        <p>
            The web has an extraordinary depth of free, open-source and independently-published games —
            from 13-kilobyte jam entries to full multiplayer RPGs. But discovery is broken: the good ones
            are scattered across GitHub, itch.io, personal blogs and jam archives, with no consistent way
            to find, evaluate, or learn how to play them. ArcadeBloom exists to fix that.
        </p>
        <p>
            Every entry in our catalogue has a verifiable source: an author name, a canonical play URL, and
            a licence. We link out with <code>rel="nofollow"</code> and transparent attribution. If we cannot
            verify where a game came from, we do not list it.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="glass-card p-6 mt-10">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">What you will find here</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-white/80">
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-fuchsia-400">▸</span> Independent reviews of browser games, written by humans</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-fuchsia-400">▸</span> How-to-play guides covering controls and strategy</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-fuchsia-400">▸</span> Transparent source attribution and licensing for every entry</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-fuchsia-400">▸</span> Direct links to the original author's site — never a re-hosted copy</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="glass-card p-6 mt-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">What you will not find</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-white/80">
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-white/40">✕</span> Re-hosted or iframe-embedded copies of other people's games</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-white/40">✕</span> Fabricated play counts or ratings</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-white/40">✕</span> Entries without a verifiable author or source</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

